protected static enum CcddConstants.DefaultColumn extends Enum<CcddConstants.DefaultColumn>
Default table types and column names. The column names flagged as protected are inherent to the specified table type and are not allowed to be altered by the user

  • Constructor Details

    • DefaultColumn

      private DefaultColumn(String tableType, String columnName, String description, CcddConstants.DefaultInputType inputType, boolean isRequiredForType, boolean isRowValueUnique, boolean isInputRequired, boolean isStructureAllowed, boolean isPointerAllowed, boolean isInputTypeUnique)
      Default table types and column names constructor
      Parameters:
      tableType - Table type to which this column belongs
      columnName - Table column name
      description - Column description; this is used as the column's tool tip text
      inputType - Column input type (DefaultInputType)
      isRequiredForType - True if this column is required in order to define a table type. Tables that include all of the required columns for a table type are considered a table of this type
      isRowValueUnique - True if this parameter must be unique in this column of this table. The user can change this flag in the type editor
      isInputRequired - True if this parameter requires a data value. This flag is used to determine if the cell in the table is highlighted when empty; it does not enforce entering a value. The user can change this flag in the type editor
      isStructureAllowed - True if the the column applies to structure data types. The user can change this flag in the type editor
      isPointerAllowed - True if the the column applies to pointer data types. The user can change this flag in the type editor
      isInputTypeUnique - True if this parameter's input type must be unique in its table type
